{"lastModified":1773085326440,"uri":"c::7584683786::vessel::d5cbd357-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744","yachtType":["Motor"],"description":"Operating Area: France, Italy, Corsica, Sardinia, Naples\n\nThere are few yachts that perfectly combine refined design, timeless elegance, and unmatched comfort. Sensei is one of them, and it is certainly one of the best examples available on the charter market today.\n\nOriginally conceived and engineered by Mitsubishi Heavy Industries to meet the high standards of the Japanese NKK Classification society, the 39m (128') M/Y Sensei, meaning “teacher” in Japanese, underwent a substantial refit and extension at Admiral Marine in the U.S Pacific under the direction of award-winning designer Glade Johnson.\n\nSubsequently, a second comprehensive refit between 2006 and 2007 at the Benetti shipyard in Italy elevated Sensei to new heights, featuring new teak decks and an extended sun deck.\n\nIn a recent overhaul by Ou Baholyodhin, Sensei has undergone a complete refurbishment, emerging with a rejuvenated and modern aesthetic. The vessel now exudes a fresh and contemporary charm, showcasing a renewed sense of style and sophistication.\n\nAdditionally, in 2024, a new zero-speed stabilization system, complete with an adaptive at-rest function, was seamlessly integrated, further enhancing the yacht's comfort and stability.","blueprint":{"name":"SENSEI","images":["/media/media::image::c::7584683786::vessel::d5cbd357-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::c7ae5b30-e6d1-11ee-bdab-8bbc3a3ac569.jpeg/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::7584683786::vessel::d5cbd357-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::2f853540-e6cc-11ee-9498-69e68ec84e26.jpeg/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::7584683786::vessel::d5cbd357-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::2f855c50-e6cc-11ee-9498-69e68ec84e26.jpeg/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::7584683786::vessel::d5cbd357-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::2f83fcc0-e6cc-11ee-9498-69e68ec84e26.jpeg/{imageVarian